5000|$|Let E be a nonarchimedean {{local field}} of {{characteristic}} not 2, with its quotient field of charcateristic p. Let F be a quadratic extension over E. Let V ( [...] resp. W [...] ) be a n-dimensional hermitian space ( [...] resp. a m-dimensional hermitian space) over F. We assume further G(V) ( [...] resp. H(W) [...] ) {{to be the}} isometry group of V ( [...] resp. W [...] ). There exists a Weil representation associated to a non-trivial <b>additive</b> <b>character</b> ψ of F for the pair G(V)×H(W), which we write as ρ(ψ). Let π be a irreducible admissible representation of G(V). Here, we only consider the case G(V)×H(W) = SO(n)×SO(m) or U(n)×U(m). We can find a certain representation θ(π,ψ) of H(W), which {{is in fact a}} certain quotient of the Weil representation ρ(ψ) by π. Now we are ready to state the conjecture of Howe.|$|E
